{{SupportPage|http://www.zoomtel.com/techsupport/adsl/5790.shtml}} "BCM63281", "V3.0", and a lead-free logo would appear to be silkscreened on the board in the FCC photos. :The board would appear to be the same as used by the [[innoband 8520-B1]].. and whatever original '''Tenda''' models these are derived from. Default settings are per '''Zoom''''s manual and the FCC sample label. The power supply shown in the FCC photos is a '''Shenzhen Hewishun Network Technology''' ('''Tenda''') TEA09U-09100 (100-240VAC ~ 50/60Hz, 0.3A -> 9VDC, 1.0A).
